OL,3,CHolocaust survivor's memorial bench
OL,4,Cdestroyed in 'act of hatred'
OL,6,FIt was unveiled in 2019, two years
OL,7,Fafter his death at the age of 94 and
OL,8,Fincluded an audio recording of his
OL,9,Fmemories of the Holocaust which has
OL,10,Falso been destroyed.
OL,12,FThe destruction of the bench was
OL,13,Fquickly labelled as a "act of
OL,14,Fantisemitic hatred" by a number of
OL,15,Fjewish organisations.
OL,17,FThe Board of Deputies of British Jews
OL,18,Fsaid: "This is a... deliberate attack
OL,19,Fon the memory and human dignity of
OL,20,FHolocaust survivor Chaim Ferster.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
