OL,4,Cdestroyed in 'act of hatred'
OL,6,F"This despicable act shows why we must
OL,7,Falways stand up to Jew hatred and
OL,8,Fchallenge all those who seek to
OL,9,Fdestroy us. We are not Jews with
OL,10,Ftrembling knees."
OL,12,FChaim Ferster was forced from his home
OL,13,Fin Poland by the Nazis as a teenage
OL,14,Fboy and spent much of the Second World
OL,15,FWar in Auschwitz. During that time, he
OL,16,Fwas subjected to malnutrition and
OL,17,Ftyphus.
OL,19,FAfter the war, he moved to England in
OL,20,F1946 with his sister Manya to start a
OL,21,Fnew life in Cheetham Hill.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
